[Mai 2012] ===================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #322)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Installation of ChessBase fonts integrated.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #320)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* HTML widget (C++): double buffering fixed.

* HTML widget (Tcl): centering mode a bit reworked.

* New help pages: File selection box, overview browser.

* Controls to main window added for full-screen mode: close, restore,
minimize.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #318)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Option -nocase added to "<treectrl> item sort itemDesc ?option ...?".

* cdb2sci added. This executable is converting any Scidb database to .sci
format.

* New option -fixedwidth added to html widget (C++).

* Html (Tcl) widget reworked. The widget it not using the scrolled frame
anymore. This change is saving resources in a highly significant way.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #316)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Color map support in tk_ogl.cpp removed.

* Bug in player dictionary fixed.

* Compiler flag "__WIN32__" preferred over "WIN32".

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #315)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Swedish translation for Rybka Aquarium support added (thanks to Lars).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #312)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Automatic detection of character set while encoding si3/si4 games. An info
message will be displayed if the detected charset differs from the charset of
the database.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #311)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Game browser: Full-screen mode implemented.

* HTML widget: attempt to fix box drawing (grep DONT_FIX_BOX_DRAWING).

* HTML widget: first attempt to fix line breaking (function fixLineBreak()).

* sci_encoder.cpp: writing tags fixed (missing nul byte in some cases).

* sci_decoder.cpp: preliminary fix for missing nul bytes (grep SCI_TAGS_FIX).

* Severe bug in namebase fixed. Compiler flag SCI_NAMEBASE_FIX will be used
temporary until a new database version is established.

[April 2012] =================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #310)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Rating files updated: ELO, DWZ, ECF, ICCF.

* Missing titles added: CILM = Corres. Lady IM (ICCF), CLGM = Corr. Lady GM
(ICCF). Possibly this requires a new database version, but the current version
is a beta version only, it's only a minor problem. The new database version
will come at least with the first alpha release.

* Bug in load function fixed: Scidb will load DWZ, ECF, and ICCF again.

* Bug in configure script shuld be fixed: now version 8.5 will be preferred
over 8.6, if exisiting.

* Archiving fixed: new version is archving directories.

* File selection box fixed: now will work properly with non-KDE systems.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #306)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Bug in PGN parser fixed (thanks to Steve).

* Swedish language file updated (thanks to Lars).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #301)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Save/replace dialog tweaked: the user may select the fields which will be
taken from the match list.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #300)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Patch of TkGrabState() tweaked. Now this function really takes the full
widget hierarchy into account. I've sent this patch to the (usually
non-interested) Tk team.

