[December 2011] ==============================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #164)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Game/Event/Player/Annotator list: Mouse wheel bindings.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #161)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* The current status about Debian Wheezy/Ubuntu Oneric:
On Debian Wheezy the workaround is working, on Ubuntu Oneric not. This means
that the hack is required only for Ubuntu Oneric. In both cases it's a problem
with the linker. The GNU team has changed the linker concept (the .ctors
section is gone), and this linker is not working properly.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #160)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Static object initialization is not working at all on Debian Wheezy/Ubuntu
Oneric. This means that the GNU compiler is not properly working on these
systems. Therefore I rolled back to the special hack (calling the constructors
by hand).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #158)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Finally I've found a proper work-around for this Debian Wheezy/Ubuntu
Oneiric problem with uninitialized static objects (hopefully; needs testing).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #155)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* There is no proper fix for the Debian Wheezy/Ubuntu 11.10 problem. I've
implemented a hack only for these insane systems (not yet tested).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #152)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Segmentation fault (hopefully) on Ubuntu 11.10/Debian Wheezy fixed. It is
a serious problem with static object initialization (on system side).

* Some implementation for LaTeX print/export.

* Configure script and make files tweaked.

